          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-17 19:36:46" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to expressions which are not to be understood literally, but symbolically or figuratively</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>symbolically</Gloss>
                <Gloss>allegorically</Gloss>
                <Gloss>figuratively</Gloss>
                <Gloss>so to speak</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages it may be more satisfactory to translate ἐν παραβολῇ and πνευματικῶς[c] by a negative expression, for example, ‘not literally’ or ‘not really.’ The expression in {S:06601100800028} might be translated as ‘that city might be called Sodom, but it isn’t really Sodom.’</Comments>
